setup/3_tor.html.body:
Set up tor with meek
dependencies: tor, meek, go
1.Download meek, use proxy in censored regions
git clone https://git.torproject.org/pluggable-transports/meek.git

2.Install go
sudo yum install go

3.Download meek dependency, use proxy in censored regions
git config --global http.proxy socks5h://127.0.0.1:1080
http_proxy=socks5h://127.0.0.1:1080 go get git.torproject.org/pluggable-transports/goptlib.git
git config --global --unset http.proxy

4.Build meek client
cd ~/meek/meek-cilent
go build
sudo cp meek-client /etc/tor/

5.Configure torrc
sudo vim /etc/tor/torrc

minimum torrc configurations:
UseBridges 1
Bridge meek 0.0.2.0:3
ClientTransportPlugin meek exec ./meek-client --url=https://meek.azureedge.net/ --front=ajax.aspnetcdn.com --log meek-client.log

tor

setup/4_openconnect.html.title: OpenConnect
setup/4_openconnect.html.body:
Set up ocserv docker
dependencies: docker, openconnect
1.Download docker
git clone https://github.com/TommyLau/docker-ocserv.git

2.Change Dockerfile
...
# change key server
&& gpg --keyserver hkp://ipv4.pool.sks-keyservers.net --recv-key 7F343FA7 \
&& gpg --keyserver hkp://ipv4.pool.sks-keyservers.net --recv-key 96865171 \
...
# change expose port
&& sed -i 's/tcp-port = 443/tcp-port = 4433/' /etc/ocserv/ocserv.conf \
&& sed -i 's/udp-port = 443/udp-port = 4433/' /etc/ocserv/ocserv.conf \
...

3.Build
docker build -t newocserv .

4.Run server
docker run --name newocserv --privileged -p 4433:4433 -p 4433:4433/udp -d newocserv

5.Test client
sudo yum install openconnect
sudo openconnect --protocol=anyconnect https://xxx.xxx.xxx.xxx:port

setup/5_openvpn.html.title: OpenVPN
setup/5_openvpn.html.body:
Set up openvpn docker
dependencies: docker,openvpn
1.Download docker
docker pull kylemanna/openvpn

2.Create
OVPN_DATA="ovpn-data-example"
docker volume create --name $OVPN_DATA
docker run -v $OVPN_DATA:/etc/openvpn --log-driver=none --rm kylemanna/openvpn ovpn_genconfig -u udp://IP:1194
docker run -v $OVPN_DATA:/etc/openvpn --log-driver=none --rm -it kylemanna/openvpn ovpn_initpki
###‚Ä¶long time
docker run -v $OVPN_DATA:/etc/openvpn -d -p 1194:1194/udp --cap-add=NET_ADMIN kylemanna/openvpn
docker run -v $OVPN_DATA:/etc/openvpn --log-driver=none --rm -it kylemanna/openvpn easyrsa build-client-full CLIENTNAME nopass
docker run -v $OVPN_DATA:/etc/openvpn --log-driver=none --rm kylemanna/openvpn ovpn_getclient CLIENTNAME > CLIENTNAME.ovpn
